Set to compete in one of the world’s toughest rallies, meet the RS Q e-tron. Our main protagonist for the 2022 @DakarRally, this alternative rally car concept is the apex of collaboration between Audi Design and Audi engineers. Created to challenge the limits and born to perform, this is the start of our Road to Dakar. 

Discover more at progress.audi

Daring to create your own track is key to progress.

In this exclusive interview, @mattiasekstromracing reveals how the “Vorsprung durch Technik” attitude has influenced motorsport and inspired his winning mindset through the years. The @dakarrally driver believes that when quattro technology arrived on the scene, it created a revolution that changed the world of racing forever. 

This is a celebration of 5 decades of the “Vorsprung durch Technik” claim. This is living progress.

#Audi #VorsprungdurchTechnik #FutureIsAnAttitude #VDT50 #emobility

Progress is in the Audi DNA.

In this exclusive interview, Oliver Hoffmann, Member of the Board for Technical Development, shares how the “Vorsprung durch Technik” claim has impacted every element of the brand, from innovative engineering to beautifully integrated design. And now, more than ever, this mindset is what shapes the future of electric mobility. 

This is a celebration of 5 decades of the “Vorsprung durch Technik” claim. This is living progress.

#Audi #VorsprungdurchTechnik #FutureIsAnAttitude #VDT50 #emobility

node.text:
Checkered flag at the @totalenergies24hoursofspa: After starting from P54, Audi Sport Team WRT, with Audi Sport drivers @kelvinvanderlinde, @dries_vanthoor1 and @charlesweerts in the #32 Audi R8 LMS, fought their way through the pack to finish runner-up after 24 hours of hard racing. 

All four of our Audi Sport teams finished within the top ten: P4 Audi Sport Team WRT #37, P6 Audi Sport Team Saintéloc #25 and P9 Audi Sport Team Attempto #66.

Well done to our teams and customers for competing in this year's endurance classic at @circuit_spa_francorchamps!
